  "text": "The neuroprotective effects are often measured as an important outcome measure in the evaluation of novel experimental treatments for experimental TBI [CITATION_1] . Neuronal and glial cell death combined with wide-spread white matter damage are likely to be detrimental and the ability of a treatment to preserve brain tissue following TBI is for obvious reasons considered to be positive. It is however important to keep in mind that the spared brain tissue may not necessarily be functionally intact. The evaluation of novel treatments therefore ultimately has to rely on behavioral tests as well.",
